The paper discusses the implementation of a time synchronization scheme in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the issue of limited computational resources of sensor nodes, which is relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed scheme involves timestamping and synchronization-related computations, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
